124
00:11:15,566 --> 00:11:16,600
Yes!

125
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,733
And all of this is based on true story, isn't it?

126
00:11:20,066 --> 00:11:21,333
Yes, sure.

127
00:11:21,366 --> 00:11:23,333
Look! What parts aren't real?

128
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:32,300
[AKSORN’s heart beats.
He wonders how he truly feels…]

129
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:35,000
[He couldn't understand why the eyes of the man on the other side of the mirror had such an effect on his heart's rhythm.]

130
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:56,933
So you do believe this is real, isn't it?

131
00:11:58,533 --> 00:11:59,333
Yes, of course.

132
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,200
Anyway...

133
00:12:17,133 --> 00:12:19,600
Let's focus on the writer

134
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:23,466
Yeah, I think so...

135
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:29,566
Do you think it's possible...

136
00:12:30,366 --> 00:12:32,866
that this person comes from the future?

137
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:35,766
Hold on for a moment.

138
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:43,666
Just the parallel universe and the story is already strange enough. Let's not jump to the conclusion that someone from the future is involved.

139
00:12:47,466 --> 00:12:48,266
However...

140
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:49,900
I sent an email to this writer

141
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,000
We should have an answer soon.

142
00:12:58,433 --> 00:12:59,233
And...

143
00:13:00,266 --> 00:13:01,433
About what you read earlier...

144
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,100
is it true or not?

145
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,566
